## 1. Program Design: How “Instant Employees” Work

- Role:
  - Anyone at home becomes a “Tap919 Runner”:
    - They share links, onboard accounts, or deploy pre‑built agents for businesses.
    - Every dollar of AI usage those accounts generate routes through Tap919 Middleman.
- Pay:
  - Revenue share on usage:
    - X–Y% of net revenue from the tenants they originate (recurring, not one‑time). [partnershipleaders](https://partnershipleaders.com/post/api-monetization-strategies-and-best-practices/)
    - Optional bounties for first‑time activation (e.g., first $50 in spend).
- Mechanics:
  - Each Runner gets:
    - Unique affiliate code and link.
    - A catalog of “Ready‑To‑Run” Tap919 agent bundles (e.g., “Ecom Support Agent”, “Lead Qualifier”).
    - A simple Runner dashboard (AetherDesk view) showing:
      - Accounts they’ve originated.
      - Usage and expected payout.
- Why this hits:
  - SaaS affiliate programs already win with recurring commission on subscriptions. [payproglobal](https://payproglobal.com/answers/what-is-saas-affiliate-program/)
  - You upgrade that to **recurring commission on usage**, which maps perfectly to your billing core. [stripe](https://stripe.com/resources/more/usage-based-pricing-for-saas-how-to-make-the-most-of-this-pricing-model)

